      </accessrestrict>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_cdb02e1719b1065a1d2f47a9568940a0">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The bulk of the papers consist of a bound volume of reprints of scientific articles by Leigh Page published between 1884 and 1952. The remaining items are: clippings on his work, three obituary articles, four photographs, including one with Niels Bohr and John Zeleny, and two letters (carbon copies) from his son, Thornton Leigh Page, to W. James King, director of the American Institute of Physics, giving a biographical sketch of his father's life.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
